WEBVTT

00:32.520 --> 00:33.630
We gave two liters of saline on the way over.

00:33.630 --> 00:35.990
BP is 80. Over 50 Multiple gunshot wounds.

00:35.990 --> 00:37.340
Gunshot wounds?

00:41.570 --> 00:42.490
Call the CS department.

00:42.490 --> 00:43.590
I'm here.

00:43.590 --> 00:44.660
Go check the other patient.

00:47.440 --> 00:48.920
What have we got?

01:18.580 --> 01:19.840
Shi Jin!

01:20.080 --> 01:22.480
Look at me! Please look at me!

01:23.140 --> 01:25.080
Can you hear me?

01:25.670 --> 01:27.250
How can you come to me like this?

01:27.980 --> 01:29.390
Please hang in there.

01:41.330 --> 01:45.250
Captain An Jeong Joon! What are you doing here?

01:46.130 --> 01:47.550
I couldn't trust my own team.

01:47.550 --> 01:49.310
So I came all the way to my friend to get help.

01:51.740 --> 01:54.660
Send me back to the North.

01:55.690 --> 01:57.940
You want to go back to the North?

02:38.570 --> 02:40.070
This is Bravo 567 Zone.

02:40.100 --> 02:41.490
-Shots fired!
-Shots fired!

02:41.490 --> 02:42.810
I need backup! I need backup!

02:43.020 --> 02:44.670
I think their target is Captain An.

03:18.320 --> 03:19.570
Cardiac arrest.

03:20.280 --> 03:22.340
150 joules! Charge!

03:22.340 --> 03:23.290
- Clear!
- Shoot!

03:25.820 --> 03:26.829
200 joules! Charge!

03:26.829 --> 03:27.720
200 joules! Charge!

03:27.720 --> 03:28.470
Shoot!

03:32.410 --> 03:35.640
His vitals aren't coming back.

03:37.829 --> 03:40.680
One, two, three!

03:42.060 --> 03:43.840
Come back!

03:45.420 --> 03:46.880
Please come back!

03:58.140 --> 03:59.410
Do you have any bullets left?

04:00.530 --> 04:01.480
I have one bullet.

04:01.480 --> 04:02.400
I'll stop the car!

04:03.550 --> 04:04.790
Ten meters.

04:05.320 --> 04:06.570
Five meters.

04:07.010 --> 04:08.470
Now!

04:59.900 --> 05:00.830
Don't do this!

05:03.030 --> 05:04.150
You can't do this to me!

05:04.800 --> 05:05.990
Please.

05:07.680 --> 05:11.260
Please pull yourself together, you jerk!

05:18.970 --> 05:20.360
It hurts like a son of a gun.

05:20.990 --> 05:23.990
His pulse is back.

05:24.860 --> 05:26.370
Shi Jin, are you awake?

05:27.200 --> 05:29.850
-Where am I?
-Can you see me?

05:30.530 --> 05:31.660
Can you hear me?

05:33.810 --> 05:34.800
Where's Captain An?

05:35.610 --> 05:36.580
What?

05:37.420 --> 05:42.450
The guy who came with me.

05:44.030 --> 05:46.180
Is he alive?

05:47.020 --> 05:48.280
Who the heck is he?

05:48.650 --> 05:49.840
Huh?

05:50.850 --> 05:52.560
You're in no position to worry about him.

05:53.159 --> 05:55.110
You almost died.

05:55.480 --> 05:57.480
If I couldn't resuscitate you within one more minute,

05:57.480 --> 05:58.880
you'd be dead by now.

06:00.190 --> 06:01.730
You're exceptionally

06:02.450 --> 06:04.520
pretty today.

06:04.520 --> 06:06.120
You jerk!

06:11.700 --> 06:15.080
The gunshot wound patient who came in with me...

06:15.080 --> 06:16.770
You can't get up now.

06:16.770 --> 06:18.170
Who is he?

06:18.440 --> 06:20.440
Did you fight with him?

06:20.770 --> 06:22.430
Is he the one who shot you?

06:22.430 --> 06:25.010
No.He's my friend.

06:26.430 --> 06:28.000
My friend I'm not so close to.

06:28.430 --> 06:29.660
Where is he?

06:32.970 --> 06:34.659
The patient who came with Captain Yoo

06:34.659 --> 06:36.480
is causing a lot of trouble.

06:38.060 --> 06:39.850
Oh my! Oh my!

06:44.000 --> 06:45.360
Don't come closer.

06:45.920 --> 06:48.300
If you touch me, I'll kill you all.

06:48.300 --> 06:50.070
If I don't touch you now,

06:50.070 --> 06:51.640
you'll die before you kill anyone.

06:52.110 --> 06:54.270
You've lost too much blood.

06:54.960 --> 06:56.120
Shut up!

06:59.200 --> 07:01.200
I'll drop my gun.

07:01.590 --> 07:03.360
You should get treated by the doctor first.

07:04.070 --> 07:06.350
How can I trust a doctor from the South?

07:07.080 --> 07:09.830
Can you guarantee I'll come out of the OR alive?

07:09.830 --> 07:12.750
You'd be more worried about being outside of the OR.

07:13.540 --> 07:14.460
if I were you,

07:14.460 --> 07:15.660
whether you're from the North or South,

07:17.730 --> 07:19.470
only doctors can save your life.

07:19.470 --> 07:20.550
Go away!

07:22.400 --> 07:23.740
Don't move.

07:29.920 --> 07:30.680
He's in shock from heavy bleeding.

07:30.680 --> 07:32.270
Dr. Song is standing by in OR Number 4.

07:32.270 --> 07:33.300
He's coming right up.

07:36.150 --> 07:37.080
Let me ask you a favor.

07:38.860 --> 07:42.200
Can you perform the operation on him?

07:44.530 --> 07:45.430
Listen to me carefully.

07:45.580 --> 07:46.940
When his X-ray's done,

07:46.940 --> 07:48.430
tie him to his bed.

07:48.430 --> 07:50.140
If there are any broken bones, put a cast on them.

07:50.570 --> 07:51.500
If he resists, beat him up.

07:56.450 --> 07:58.900
There's no sign of pneumothorax or heart strain.

07:59.330 --> 08:01.310
His heartbeat is normal.

08:04.080 --> 08:04.970
Scalpel.

08:17.670 --> 08:19.600
What's this? It's not a gunshot wound.

08:20.200 --> 08:21.320
There's something inside.

08:22.990 --> 08:23.810
Captain An Jeong Joon's

08:23.810 --> 08:26.230
is from the North Korean Special Mission Force

08:26.230 --> 08:28.340
and is with the Security Services now.

08:28.870 --> 08:31.710
I heard that he's on leave during these second round of talks.

08:32.929 --> 08:33.909
A guy who's on leave showed up

08:33.909 --> 08:36.950
in the middle of Seoul and started a gunfight?

08:36.950 --> 08:38.750
Captain An was being chased.

08:39.970 --> 08:41.640
Those guys were after Captain An.

08:41.860 --> 08:43.830
Judging from the way they were armed,

08:44.169 --> 08:46.600
how they moved, and how they kidnapped the victim,

08:46.600 --> 08:48.420
they're professionals trained for special ops.

08:49.050 --> 08:50.560
They're not from America.

08:50.560 --> 08:52.560
They're from somewhere near Russia.

08:52.560 --> 08:54.060
We've identified them.

08:54.060 --> 08:56.930
They're military officers from the Matoponian embassy.

08:56.930 --> 08:58.400
Embassy military officers?

08:58.400 --> 08:59.360
Yes.

08:59.360 --> 09:00.310
When Captain An entered the country,

09:00.310 --> 09:02.200
he used a fake Matoponian passport.

09:02.200 --> 09:03.950
That's why they were after him.

09:04.380 --> 09:05.550
The embassy officers opened fire because of a fake passport?

09:05.550 --> 09:07.580
They could've come up with a better excuse.

09:08.900 --> 09:10.560
I feel bad for you guys.

09:10.560 --> 09:12.370
We have no right to detain them

09:12.370 --> 09:14.920
under international law.

09:15.440 --> 09:17.840
We need to investigate Captain An, whom we have custody of.

09:18.460 --> 09:19.660
The hospital just called.

09:19.660 --> 09:21.880
Captain An's surgery is over now.

09:24.580 --> 09:25.670
How did it go?

09:25.900 --> 09:26.790
What?

09:27.110 --> 09:28.030
The operation.

09:30.090 --> 09:31.470
He's alive

09:31.950 --> 09:33.330
and has been moved to a recovery room.

09:33.330 --> 09:34.650
He's still unconscious.

09:36.860 --> 09:38.050
I have another patient who I saved.

09:38.570 --> 09:40.970
I guess, for him,

09:41.560 --> 09:43.610
I'm nothing more than a doctor.

09:43.990 --> 09:45.510
That doctor experienced hell

09:45.510 --> 09:47.080
when her boyfriend came in,

09:47.080 --> 09:48.160
bathed in blood

09:48.160 --> 09:50.080
and in cardiac arrest.

09:51.720 --> 09:52.630
I'm sorry.

09:52.940 --> 09:55.070
Is that it? No explanation

09:55.470 --> 09:56.590
whatsoever?

09:57.530 --> 09:59.550
Aren't you curious if I'm okay

10:00.050 --> 10:02.190
while worrying about your not-so-close friend so badly?

10:03.670 --> 10:04.670
Once you get better,

10:05.530 --> 10:06.780
I'm going to kill you.

10:08.830 --> 10:10.810
I might not give this to you.

10:12.600 --> 10:13.480
What is it?

10:15.060 --> 10:16.420
Why are you bringing him here?

10:22.920 --> 10:23.810
Sir.

10:26.540 --> 10:28.430
This room is under our control as of now.

10:29.170 --> 10:31.060
Some medical personnel are restricted as well.

10:31.060 --> 10:32.230
Please cooperate.

10:38.520 --> 10:39.990
I heard you wanted to see me.

10:41.000 --> 10:42.240
I think Captain Yoo sent me to the OR

10:42.240 --> 10:44.870
because of this.

10:44.870 --> 10:46.800
It's from the North Korean patient.

10:49.390 --> 10:50.710
-Really?
-Yes.

10:50.710 --> 10:53.170
There's a rumor that the patient is North Korean.

10:53.170 --> 10:54.560
Can we treat him?

10:54.560 --> 10:55.290
A North Korean?

10:55.290 --> 10:57.330
We should. He's hurt.

10:58.010 --> 10:59.310
We took an oath.

10:59.310 --> 11:00.660
Aren't you scared?

11:00.660 --> 11:01.800
He came in soaked in blood

11:01.800 --> 11:03.270
after being shot.

11:03.270 --> 11:05.950
He came to be in that state after hitting a signboard while drunk.

11:05.950 --> 11:06.930
I saw a lot worse things

11:06.930 --> 11:08.100
in Uruk.

11:08.980 --> 11:10.800
Everyone! Stand in line in front of the guns.

11:10.800 --> 11:12.540
Salute! Salute!

11:13.040 --> 11:14.500
Hands off!

11:14.500 --> 11:16.640
If you move, I'll shoot you.

11:19.300 --> 11:20.410
Stop bluffing!

11:20.410 --> 11:21.920
How dare you try to fool me?

11:22.790 --> 11:24.520
I want to kick your butt.

11:26.080 --> 11:27.140
News.

11:27.460 --> 11:28.240
Every time I read politicial news,

11:28.240 --> 11:29.750
I will unconsciously burst coarse.

11:29.750 --> 11:30.790
Ha Ja Ae!

11:34.050 --> 11:35.070
I heard you were held hostage.

11:35.070 --> 11:36.830
Are you okay?     Did he hurt you?

11:36.830 --> 11:39.660
Where is that jerk? I'm going to kill him.

11:39.700 --> 11:41.540
He was almost killed, but you just saved him.

11:41.540 --> 11:42.670
What?

11:43.490 --> 11:45.310
He was the patient I performed surgery on?

11:46.660 --> 11:47.770
I'm too nice!

11:48.950 --> 11:50.620
I'm too generous!

11:53.900 --> 11:55.040
Unbelievable!

11:55.400 --> 11:56.940
I heard your boyfriend

11:56.940 --> 11:58.440
came in covered in blood with that North Korean patient.

11:58.440 --> 12:00.800
Guys in black suits are all over the place.

12:00.800 --> 12:02.950
How can you date a guy like him?

12:02.950 --> 12:05.250
What exactly does your boyfriend do?

12:05.660 --> 12:07.200
Tell me about it.

12:07.200 --> 12:09.530
I don't know exactly what he does.

12:11.310 --> 12:12.620
I've been summoned by Mr. Han.

12:12.620 --> 12:13.710
What about these?

12:13.710 --> 12:15.700
Why isn't she getting angry at me?

12:15.700 --> 12:16.990
What are they?

12:16.990 --> 12:18.540
Belongings of the unidentified North Korean patient.

12:19.930 --> 12:21.860
Oh! Are they all made in North Korea?

12:26.670 --> 12:27.650
It's not working.

12:29.160 --> 12:32.150
When a ballpoint pen doesn't work, wet it with some saliva.

12:34.520 --> 12:35.580
Let me take these.

12:40.960 --> 12:41.840
Bye.

12:43.770 --> 12:44.770
What did he say?

12:45.510 --> 12:47.390
This isn't a regular pen.

12:47.390 --> 12:48.590
It's a poisonous pen.

12:48.590 --> 12:52.590
I almost just killed myself.

12:53.340 --> 12:55.370
Dr. Song, are you okay?

12:57.870 --> 12:58.790
Move.

13:00.720 --> 13:02.820
I said move!

13:02.820 --> 13:04.510
Why did you come to Haesung Hospital

13:04.510 --> 13:06.540
of all the hospitals in Gangnam?

13:06.540 --> 13:08.920
This is a really expensive hospital.

13:08.920 --> 13:10.890
We're carrying out government business here.

13:10.890 --> 13:12.320
Please cooperate.

13:12.320 --> 13:13.460
This is an official letter from the army.

13:13.460 --> 13:14.810
This is not how you do things!

13:14.810 --> 13:15.920
Right.

13:17.960 --> 13:20.570
Who the heck is your boyfriend

13:20.570 --> 13:22.420
and why is him being hurt government business?

13:22.730 --> 13:25.020
Who the heck is the other guy?

13:27.210 --> 13:28.050
Did the two of them fight?

13:28.860 --> 13:29.780
Who won?

13:31.520 --> 13:32.230
I don't know.

13:32.460 --> 13:33.290
He lost.

13:33.290 --> 13:34.300
I can see that he lost.

13:34.990 --> 13:36.130
He's not good at fighting.

13:36.130 --> 13:37.220
Everyone serves in the army.

13:37.620 --> 13:38.690
Did you serve in the army?

13:40.310 --> 13:41.540
What do you think?

13:41.870 --> 13:42.500
I thought you were exempted.

13:42.500 --> 13:43.910
That's not my question.

13:44.330 --> 13:46.140
Can you keep it down?

13:46.140 --> 13:47.610
You keep it down!

13:47.610 --> 13:48.830
This is my hospital.

13:50.180 --> 13:51.520
You take care of this

13:52.070 --> 13:53.500
either as his guardian

13:53.770 --> 13:55.050
or as his doctor.

13:55.530 --> 13:56.350
Okay.

13:57.210 --> 13:58.840
- Let's go.
- Yes, sir.

14:03.360 --> 14:05.610
I'm Captain Yoo Shi Jin

14:05.610 --> 14:06.950
from the Korean Special Warfare Command.

14:08.170 --> 14:09.490
Captain An Jeong Joon,

14:10.170 --> 14:11.750
what's your official position?

14:15.130 --> 14:17.620
Why did you smuggle yourself into Korea?

14:23.250 --> 14:24.630
What's your mission?

14:29.250 --> 14:30.480
Whatever your mission was,

14:31.570 --> 14:34.290
you seemed to have failed to carry it out since you ended up here.

14:34.290 --> 14:35.730
Am i right?

14:37.460 --> 14:38.720
Captain An Jeong Joon, let me ask you this

14:39.280 --> 14:41.480
under the agreement of the Geneva Convention.

14:42.300 --> 14:43.890
Are you seeking asylum in Korea?

14:48.430 --> 14:50.840
It's hard to hear his voice.

14:51.850 --> 14:54.670
If you're that shy, why didn't you stay in North Korea?

14:55.600 --> 14:57.560
Did he say anything when I wasn't around?

14:58.330 --> 14:59.490
I’ve already told you.

15:01.070 --> 15:02.490
He smuggled himself into South Korea

15:02.490 --> 15:05.300
and is asking us to send him back to the North.

15:05.300 --> 15:06.680
I don't know why,

15:07.320 --> 15:08.910
but you couldn't use official channels

15:09.340 --> 15:12.040
through China or Russia

15:12.040 --> 15:12.840
so you chose the most dangerous route,

15:12.840 --> 15:15.260
which is South Korea.

15:15.260 --> 15:16.640
If that's true,

15:16.640 --> 15:18.060
your only option is to seek asylum.

15:19.120 --> 15:20.160
If you tell us everything you know,

15:20.160 --> 15:21.740
we'll welcome you with open arms.

15:24.860 --> 15:26.600
I'll give you some time
to think,

15:26.600 --> 15:27.660
so use it well.

15:28.600 --> 15:30.350
I want you to help him make up his mind.

15:42.540 --> 15:45.420
These are the things

15:45.790 --> 15:46.720
If he's not on leave

15:46.720 --> 15:48.710
and this is an unauthorized black op.

15:48.710 --> 15:50.310
We might find the answer here.

15:55.040 --> 15:56.970
I'll take it and decrypt it as soon as possible.

16:01.490 --> 16:03.110
The summit is just around the corner.

16:04.250 --> 16:06.220
What? What are they talking about?

16:06.520 --> 16:08.010
Captain An's not saying anything,

16:08.010 --> 16:09.190
and Captain Yoo is the only one talking.

16:09.190 --> 16:10.470
What's he talking about?

16:10.880 --> 16:12.750
Is he using the mother and family cards?

16:12.750 --> 16:13.730
Well...

16:15.980 --> 16:16.840
If you sprinkle vinegar directly on the noodles,

16:16.840 --> 16:18.150
it's too sour.

16:18.150 --> 16:20.030
If you put mustard on the noodles, it's too tangy.

16:20.400 --> 16:21.410
What?

16:21.640 --> 16:22.760
They're talking about ice noodles.

16:22.760 --> 16:23.680
Captain An treated us
to ice noodle dishes

16:23.680 --> 16:25.100
at our first meeting in Pyongyang.

16:25.100 --> 16:26.790
Have you gone completely crazy?

16:29.260 --> 16:30.800
I have to report to my superiors

16:30.800 --> 16:32.220
and he's talking about mustard?

16:32.940 --> 16:34.190
He's a captain.

16:34.190 --> 16:35.880
He knows what he has to do.

16:35.880 --> 16:36.900
This jerk!

16:38.160 --> 16:39.610
Look at this!

16:39.980 --> 16:42.560
What am I going to tell him?

16:43.890 --> 16:46.550
This is Lieutenant Colonel Park Byung Soo.

16:47.240 --> 16:48.530
You're saying that

16:48.910 --> 16:50.710
we don't know anything yet?

16:52.270 --> 16:54.000
What kind of report is this?

16:55.020 --> 16:56.360
The North and South Talks are tomorrow.

16:57.510 --> 16:59.380
The North Delegation is on their way here now,

16:59.380 --> 17:01.350
one day ahead of schedule.

17:01.350 --> 17:04.410
If we don't hand Captain An over to them by tomorrow morning,

17:04.410 --> 17:06.950
they'll call off the talks.

17:06.950 --> 17:08.319
What should we do?

17:09.390 --> 17:12.609
The North Delegation has passed the Jayuro Road and has just entered Seoul.

17:12.900 --> 17:13.930
Already?

17:14.280 --> 17:15.310
How fast!

17:15.310 --> 17:16.369
Is Pyongyang that close from Seoul?

17:18.480 --> 17:19.760
Okay.

17:20.550 --> 17:21.810
Hello.

17:21.810 --> 17:23.920
If you get anything, let me know immediately.

17:24.210 --> 17:25.530
Okay.

17:27.150 --> 17:30.170
He's not even one of the top three officials in North Korea.

17:30.920 --> 17:33.280
Because of a mere captain like him,

17:33.280 --> 17:36.540
all the high officials both in the North and South are working all night long.

17:38.000 --> 17:40.210
Does it make sense to you?

17:40.210 --> 17:42.530
Who the heck is this Captain An fellow?

17:42.970 --> 17:44.810
Captain An is probably a murder suspect

17:44.810 --> 17:47.610
wanted by Interpol.

17:48.400 --> 17:49.820
A murder suspect?

17:50.300 --> 17:51.730
He's not a terrorist or an assassin?

17:51.730 --> 17:53.380
Two days ago,

17:53.380 --> 17:55.430
a very important witness of a crime

17:55.430 --> 17:58.040
committed by a Yakuza organization

17:58.040 --> 18:00.300
was shot from a long distance while on his way to court to testify.

18:00.300 --> 18:01.820
Is Captain An the suspect?

18:01.820 --> 18:02.770
No.

18:03.020 --> 18:05.800
The suspect was found dead in the next building

18:05.800 --> 18:07.230
Where is the suspected assassination point.

18:07.230 --> 18:10.320
Captain An is as

18:10.320 --> 18:11.650
second murder suspect being wanted.

18:11.650 --> 18:14.060
Who's this guy Captain An killed?

18:14.890 --> 18:17.010
He's someone we all know.

18:22.390 --> 18:23.630
Sergeant Lee Seok Jin.

18:23.630 --> 18:24.480
He was in the Special Mission Force with Captain An.

18:24.480 --> 18:26.890
He assassinated a former fellow soldier

18:26.890 --> 18:29.940
who was involved in a Yakuza organization.

18:29.940 --> 18:31.870
I think that was Captain An's mission.

18:31.870 --> 18:32.860
But why?

18:34.570 --> 18:35.430
Did you find out

18:35.430 --> 18:37.110
what's on the SD chip that we found in Captain An's body?

18:37.220 --> 18:38.890
The code is too complicated,

18:38.890 --> 18:40.610
so it'll take about a week to break it.

18:40.610 --> 18:44.780
But North Korea wants Captain An back by tomorrow morning.

18:44.780 --> 18:46.170
And we have no reason not to return him.

18:47.420 --> 18:48.470
That means we don't have a lot of time.

18:48.470 --> 18:49.370
The fastest way

18:49.370 --> 18:50.830
is to make Captain An talk.

18:51.570 --> 18:53.140
He knows that the room is bugged,

18:53.140 --> 18:54.830
so he won't talk about anything important.

18:54.830 --> 18:55.670
We need to

18:55.670 --> 18:57.100
use his mother or sister,

18:57.100 --> 18:58.860
who both live in North Korea.

19:00.380 --> 19:01.890
We have to find another way.

19:01.890 --> 19:03.380
We need Dr. Kang's help

19:04.190 --> 19:05.630
and the SD chip.

19:06.170 --> 19:08.870
The SD chip that the NIS is analyzing at the moment?

19:08.870 --> 19:10.200
It'll be hard to get, right?

19:12.080 --> 19:13.790
We made a mistake.

19:13.790 --> 19:15.690
We should've made a copy.

19:17.780 --> 19:19.580
Are you talking about something like this?

19:22.360 --> 19:23.840
What a thorough man you are!

19:23.840 --> 19:26.150
Should I send Dr. Kang up to your room?

19:27.460 --> 19:28.680
You have some bone fragments

19:28.680 --> 19:29.740
that weren't removed from previous injuries

19:29.740 --> 19:32.270
stuck to your wrist and thigh

19:32.270 --> 19:34.380
and you have four gunshot wounds.

19:34.380 --> 19:35.880
They're all from today's incident.

19:41.190 --> 19:42.660
The most serious case

19:42.660 --> 19:45.620
is this old piece right next to your spine.

19:45.620 --> 19:47.850
If you don't get rid of it, it could touch the dura mater

19:47.850 --> 19:51.480
and paralyze you from the waist down, Captain An.

19:53.710 --> 19:55.630
What I'm saying is that

19:56.470 --> 19:57.560
you're lucky to be alive.

19:57.560 --> 19:59.130
Please don't behave

19:59.600 --> 20:01.450
like you have nine lives. I know someone just like you in South Korea.

20:03.090 --> 20:04.560
Someone as crazy as you.

20:07.550 --> 20:09.880
I wasn't going to say this,

20:09.880 --> 20:12.330
but that soldier guy from Uruk.

20:14.680 --> 20:15.460
Who do you mean?

20:15.460 --> 20:16.530
That guy. He yelled at me

20:16.530 --> 20:17.680
because I operated on a dying man

20:17.680 --> 20:19.140
and locked you up.

20:19.140 --> 20:20.160
And he punished Captain.

20:20.160 --> 20:21.910
He looks like a rockfish.

20:21.910 --> 20:23.910
I saw him earlier and he was bossing around

20:23.910 --> 20:25.620
our hospital staff while yelling at them.

20:25.620 --> 20:26.700
Does he think that he's in charge of this...

20:26.700 --> 20:28.430
Nonsense!

20:28.430 --> 20:30.060
What are you doing?

20:44.910 --> 20:45.920
What should I do?

20:56.520 --> 20:57.810
What I meant is that

20:57.810 --> 21:00.480
he must've noticed

21:00.480 --> 21:02.310
how happy I was to see him again.

21:02.590 --> 21:04.870
I almost ran to him and hugged him.

21:05.170 --> 21:06.210
I'm sure he knows.

21:06.640 --> 21:08.150
He's such a sweet man.

21:08.150 --> 21:10.300
He's the sweetest.

21:10.300 --> 21:12.050
How's your mother doing?

21:12.200 --> 21:13.110
Good.

21:13.110 --> 21:15.130
She always makes a big deal out of it

21:15.130 --> 21:18.030
when she makes dishes using my own money.

21:19.200 --> 21:22.190
I need a place to talk to Captain An privately.

21:23.360 --> 21:25.320
She's doing just fine.

21:28.960 --> 21:30.260
I didn't say good-bye properly the other day.

21:31.140 --> 21:32.180
I want to see her again.

21:32.660 --> 21:34.120
You can choose a place.

21:36.590 --> 21:38.180
Do I have to?

21:39.410 --> 21:40.950
I don't want to

21:41.450 --> 21:43.390
and my mother wouldn't want to, either.

21:46.690 --> 21:48.100
You have nothing to worry about.

21:49.850 --> 21:51.800
I don't trust you.

21:54.920 --> 21:57.020
Please.

22:04.440 --> 22:05.680
Don't dump me

22:05.680 --> 22:06.700
like that because I'm drunk.

22:08.270 --> 22:10.890
Captain An, come to the CT room in half an hour.

22:10.890 --> 22:12.610
I need to run some more tests.

22:13.880 --> 22:15.330
Don't be late.

22:15.330 --> 22:16.500
I have a tight schedule.

22:33.200 --> 22:34.370
Oh my!

22:37.200 --> 22:38.230
Lieutenant Colonel?

22:38.360 --> 22:40.370
I didn't expect to see you here.

22:40.370 --> 22:42.590
It's so nice to see you again.

22:42.970 --> 22:44.630
You don't have to hug me.

22:44.630 --> 22:45.590
What?

22:46.220 --> 22:48.270
Why do we run into each other

22:48.270 --> 22:49.560
when our nation is in crisis?

22:49.810 --> 22:51.040
Tell me about it.

22:51.040 --> 22:52.130
Excuse me.

23:06.950 --> 23:08.490
What is it? What's going on?

23:08.490 --> 23:10.170
I have a lot of patients waiting for me.

23:10.680 --> 23:11.800
10 minutes.

23:11.800 --> 23:14.430
This is the only place that I can be sure isn't bugged.

23:14.840 --> 23:16.510
Bugged?

23:17.030 --> 23:18.360
What are you talking about?

23:18.360 --> 23:19.840
You don't need to know for your own safety.

23:20.170 --> 23:21.400
I'm working

23:21.400 --> 23:23.430
for our nation at the moment.

23:24.190 --> 23:25.160
Does our nation know

23:25.160 --> 23:26.380
that you're working for it?

23:26.380 --> 23:27.270
Shh!

23:28.110 --> 23:29.760
You have to promise me one thing.

23:29.760 --> 23:31.590
Even if my nation denies me,

23:31.940 --> 23:33.790
I want you to remember me.

23:33.790 --> 23:34.850
I'm going to kill you.

23:35.690 --> 23:36.760
What's it about?

23:36.760 --> 23:37.610
Shh.

23:42.560 --> 23:43.880
We're not bugged here.

23:43.880 --> 23:45.160
You can tell me anything.

23:50.460 --> 23:51.870
I'm doing this

23:51.870 --> 23:53.200
behind my boss's back.

23:54.300 --> 23:56.250
I only have about 10 minutes.

23:56.250 --> 23:57.700
I'm offering you help.

23:58.320 --> 24:00.450
This is your last chance.

24:07.120 --> 24:08.660
What's the problem?

24:10.870 --> 24:12.680
Sergeant Lee Seok Jin.

24:15.110 --> 24:16.720
Why did you kill him?

24:18.500 --> 24:20.680
Give me my stuff back.

24:25.930 --> 24:27.340
Are you looking for this?

24:34.350 --> 24:36.720
It's my turn to get answers.

24:38.710 --> 24:41.660
What's on it?

24:50.970 --> 24:53.190
I got this tip that the North Korean

24:53.190 --> 24:54.640
Special Mission Force Soldiers who were trained

24:55.800 --> 24:58.360
to fight for our country were hired as hit men

24:58.360 --> 25:01.400
for criminal organizations, such as the Yakuza or mafia

25:01.400 --> 25:04.030
in mercenary markets.

25:06.200 --> 25:07.830
Polaris 13 completed the mission.

25:07.830 --> 25:09.260
Check if the money's been wired.

25:09.800 --> 25:10.910
My job was to kill the ones

25:11.280 --> 25:13.740
who betrayed our country

25:14.590 --> 25:17.010
and find out who was behind it.

25:18.630 --> 25:21.760
Do you have evidence that'll prove who's behind it?

25:23.200 --> 25:24.520
I'm not falling for your leading question.

25:28.920 --> 25:30.430
I know you’ve already seen what's on it.

25:32.840 --> 25:35.250
The password is so complicated.

25:35.810 --> 25:36.980
What's the password?

25:37.910 --> 25:42.080
It'd be better if you just told me what's on it.

25:46.190 --> 25:47.230
Never mind.

25:47.850 --> 25:50.670
What happens in the Republic

25:50.670 --> 25:52.120
gets solved in the Republic.

25:53.900 --> 25:55.330
The Republic has already started doing something.

25:59.130 --> 26:00.550
Director Choi from the National Security Agency is

26:01.670 --> 26:04.080
on his way, ahead of schedule.

26:06.440 --> 26:08.360
We have to hand you over

26:10.130 --> 26:13.610
to them tomorrow morning.

26:22.370 --> 26:24.080
Have they bugged this place as well?

26:25.990 --> 26:27.310
No. Not here.

26:29.020 --> 26:30.980
I can't even breathe in the room.

26:32.000 --> 26:33.300
The situation will end soon.

26:33.520 --> 26:34.740
Thank you for helping me earlier.

26:35.740 --> 26:37.070
I hate you.

26:38.350 --> 26:40.400
How did it go with Captain An?

26:40.400 --> 26:41.170
It went well.

26:44.180 --> 26:46.970
By the way, his name is An Jeong Joon.

26:47.270 --> 26:48.530
A Captain.

26:48.900 --> 26:51.510
Is it okay for you to tell me

26:51.510 --> 26:53.640
the name of a North Korean citizen?

26:54.190 --> 26:57.520
I want somebody to remember him by his name.

26:58.750 --> 27:03.580
Especially a brave woman like you.

27:08.810 --> 27:10.820
I gave him some painkiller and sedatives.

27:10.820 --> 27:12.650
He'll sleep for about five hours.

28:15.930 --> 28:16.940
Where are you going?

28:19.720 --> 28:23.300
You can't leave the hospital without your doctor's permission in the South.

28:25.620 --> 28:27.050
Move!

28:27.550 --> 28:29.520
I need to finish my mission.

28:29.900 --> 28:30.940
I told you that we'd hand you over

28:30.940 --> 28:33.450
to the North in the morning.

28:35.120 --> 28:39.670
Is it awkward for you to see Director Choi at the moment?

28:42.790 --> 28:45.040
I was thinking about why you came to me.

28:46.480 --> 28:48.690
We're friends separated by distance

28:49.720 --> 28:51.570
because my enemy is

28:53.650 --> 28:55.900
also your enemy?

28:58.940 --> 29:01.250
Did you betray the Republic?

29:01.250 --> 29:02.590
Or

29:03.930 --> 29:06.320
did the Republic betray you?

29:13.310 --> 29:14.670
A warrior

29:15.290 --> 29:18.380
never betrays the Republic.

29:33.310 --> 29:34.690
Who survived?

29:38.830 --> 29:44.500
Polaris or Pluto?

29:45.380 --> 29:46.750
It was Pluto.

29:46.750 --> 29:52.410
You sure are a hero of the 11th Corps.

29:53.270 --> 29:57.070
Are you the traitor?

30:02.130 --> 30:04.020
That can't be.

30:04.680 --> 30:08.990
Pluto, you're the traitor.

30:26.860 --> 30:28.170
I'm begging you.

30:30.470 --> 30:32.010
Please let me go.

30:32.010 --> 30:34.230
If you go back to the North, you'll die.

30:34.810 --> 30:37.010
It doesn't matter who betrayed whom.

30:37.010 --> 30:39.240
I have a mission to finish.

30:39.920 --> 30:41.410
If you go, you'll die.

30:41.410 --> 30:42.790
Even if that's true,

30:43.310 --> 30:44.760
I'll die in the Republic.

30:46.500 --> 30:47.620
Please let me go.

30:57.660 --> 31:00.680
I'm a soldier who serves my own country.

31:01.210 --> 31:02.760
I can't let you go.

31:03.850 --> 31:05.840
You treated me to ice noodles in Pyongyang,

31:08.060 --> 31:11.320
and I saved your life earlier today in return.

31:31.910 --> 31:33.010
This is a good-bye present.

31:34.040 --> 31:37.330
It's really good. I hope you enjoy it.

31:53.430 --> 31:55.060
Did you say good-bye to your friend?

31:56.100 --> 31:57.530
Your friend has already left.

31:57.530 --> 31:58.800
Without my permission.

31:59.410 --> 32:00.420
Through the window.

32:03.990 --> 32:05.630
I'm not close enough to say good-bye to him.

32:08.560 --> 32:10.380
It's started to hurt again.

32:10.960 --> 32:12.670
-Sit up straight!
-Yes, ma'am.

32:13.830 --> 32:15.360
Did you break the window?

32:16.270 --> 32:17.340
No, I didn't.

32:18.060 --> 32:19.680
He broke the window.

32:19.680 --> 32:21.800
Did you break the window downstairs then?

32:23.180 --> 32:24.130
He broke it as well.

32:24.130 --> 32:25.280
Then you, as his friend, will pay.

32:25.280 --> 32:27.120
Should i, as his friend, pay

32:27.120 --> 32:28.620
for the new windows?

32:30.250 --> 32:32.260
As I’ve already told you, I'm not that close to him.

32:32.260 --> 32:33.140
I had to

32:33.140 --> 32:34.760
put up with Mr. Han

32:34.760 --> 32:36.190
when he yelled at me about the broken windows.

32:36.190 --> 32:37.400
Where is he?

32:38.380 --> 32:39.390
How dare he

32:39.390 --> 32:40.260
yell at my girlfriend?

32:40.260 --> 32:42.960
Because my boyfriend is a friend of a North Korean soldier.

32:47.940 --> 32:49.550
Right. I'll be back in two hours.

32:49.550 --> 32:51.510
Finish your IV and stay right here.

32:53.080 --> 32:54.710
Don't you dare run away.

32:57.010 --> 32:57.890
Hello?

33:05.800 --> 33:07.510
Your baby is already studying anatomy.

33:08.410 --> 33:09.940
You're due in a week, right?

33:09.940 --> 33:11.700
Yes. Next week.

33:11.700 --> 33:13.760
Did you see Dr. Kang's boyfriend?

33:13.760 --> 33:14.680
I heard he's good-looking.

33:14.680 --> 33:15.960
I don't care how good-looking he is.

33:15.960 --> 33:16.970
He came in with gunshot wounds and with

33:16.970 --> 33:18.360
a North Korean soldier.

33:18.360 --> 33:20.760
I heard the North Korean soldier is also handsome.

33:21.800 --> 33:23.770
I hope we'll be unified soon.

33:26.380 --> 33:27.170
Hey!

33:30.820 --> 33:32.700
Why don't you get changed?

33:33.390 --> 33:34.890
You walk around in scrubs

33:34.890 --> 33:36.370
with a huge stomach

33:36.370 --> 33:37.820
and are making patients nervous.

33:37.820 --> 33:39.510
Do you still make your patients nervous in the OR?

33:39.510 --> 33:40.290
Have you improved your skills?

33:40.290 --> 33:42.840
Hey! You should be in your gown at all times.

33:42.840 --> 33:45.550
People might think you're a patient, not a doctor.

33:45.550 --> 33:48.350
What? What did you just say?

33:49.340 --> 33:51.420
What are you doing?

33:55.760 --> 33:57.560
My water broke. She's coming out.

33:57.560 --> 33:59.780
You said you had another week.

34:00.900 --> 34:02.550
Call Dr. Jeong from OB/GYN!

34:02.550 --> 34:03.660
The baby's coming.

34:03.660 --> 34:05.050
You wench! Let go already!

34:05.550 --> 34:07.040
Hey, harder! Harder!

34:07.250 --> 34:08.380
Push harder?

34:08.380 --> 34:09.440
No. Pull her hair harder!

34:09.440 --> 34:11.320
Hey! Ji Soo!

34:11.320 --> 34:12.060
Go, Hee Eun!

34:18.850 --> 34:19.800
Administration?

34:19.800 --> 34:21.830
Yes. I call you because of the broken windows.

34:21.830 --> 34:23.920
You're the guardian of Mr. Yoo Shi Jin.

34:24.750 --> 34:27.370
Does he look like the kind of guy who needs a guardian?

34:27.370 --> 34:29.510
One upstairs and one downstairs. Two altogether.

34:29.510 --> 34:32.010
They weren't broken by a natural disaster or an accident.

34:32.010 --> 34:33.989
Someone has to take responsibility and pay for them.

34:33.989 --> 34:35.790
I don't think I should be responsible.

34:35.790 --> 34:38.830
Mr. Han told me to get money from you.

34:39.770 --> 34:42.370
And I think that sounds quite fair as well.

34:42.750 --> 34:44.100
Clench your teeth.

34:45.010 --> 34:46.580
By the way, why are you here?

34:46.580 --> 34:49.030
I'm the doctor of the patient in the room

34:49.030 --> 34:50.630
downstairs where Yoo Shi Jin broke the window.

34:50.630 --> 34:51.500
It wasn't Yoo Shi Jin.

34:51.500 --> 34:52.889
It was the North Korean patient.

34:52.889 --> 34:55.100
But the North Korean patient went back to the North.

34:55.100 --> 34:56.239
That's why you should...

34:56.239 --> 34:57.470
Clench your teeth.

35:00.160 --> 35:00.900
Excuse me.

35:03.620 --> 35:04.390
Hello?

35:05.320 --> 35:06.290
Baby?

35:07.580 --> 35:08.530
Already?

35:08.670 --> 35:09.700
The baby's coming? Now?

35:09.700 --> 35:11.320
Yes! I'll be right over!

35:11.320 --> 35:12.360
I have to go!

35:12.360 --> 35:13.370
Go ahead!

35:13.850 --> 35:16.130
The baby's coming. Aren't you happy?

35:16.670 --> 35:18.860
Hey! Dr. Kang! Dr. Kang!

35:20.740 --> 35:22.370
The South Korean idiots always talk about

35:22.370 --> 35:26.780
family reunions and economic cooperation

35:26.780 --> 35:30.020
and say that the future of North and South Korea

35:30.330 --> 35:33.040
depends on the peace of the Korean Peninsula.

35:33.040 --> 35:36.440
However, the higher the fence, the safer it is. It's better for the North and South to stay distant.

35:38.070 --> 35:38.980
Leave us.

35:46.730 --> 35:50.670
I've been right all along.

35:54.950 --> 35:56.740
To get what you want,

35:57.140 --> 35:58.830
threats work better than discussion

35:58.830 --> 36:00.580
and tension better than peace.

36:01.780 --> 36:04.780
It's good to see your face again.

36:12.350 --> 36:15.130
Pluto 51!

36:16.650 --> 36:18.840
I'm going to report on my mission.

36:18.840 --> 36:21.020
I took care of Polaris 13 who betrayed the honor of North Korean warriors

36:22.600 --> 36:26.260
and found out who's behind this whole thing.

36:27.750 --> 36:29.160
I know.

36:30.720 --> 36:34.220
I heard you have already secured the transaction file.

36:37.200 --> 36:38.690
Where is that file?

36:42.790 --> 36:44.810
South Korea is quiet.

36:44.840 --> 36:47.260
That means they haven't broken the code yet.

36:47.960 --> 36:48.920
I guess you're keeping it

36:48.920 --> 36:51.880
somewhere in your body like you were trained.

37:06.750 --> 37:11.180
I'll bury the secret with the traitor's body forever.

37:12.660 --> 37:14.310
Any last words?

37:17.040 --> 37:21.860
Put a bowl of Pyongyang ice noodles

37:22.490 --> 37:28.000
on my memorial service day. Can you get it from Okryugwan in the Koryeo Hotel?

37:30.750 --> 37:32.270
That can be arranged.

37:35.020 --> 37:37.080
Anything else?

37:37.680 --> 37:41.520
Now I'm done, I'll finish my last mission.

37:44.440 --> 37:45.660
In the name of the Republic,

37:46.100 --> 37:47.170
I'm executing the traitor Choi Ji Ho,

37:47.170 --> 37:50.670
Director of the National Security Agency.

38:33.540 --> 38:35.420
What's this?

38:36.180 --> 38:39.150
An agreement about a family reunion center.

38:39.150 --> 38:41.900
This is what we want to be resolved first.

38:42.250 --> 38:43.680
I thought handing Captain An

38:43.680 --> 38:46.500
over was a nice enough gesture on our part.

38:46.500 --> 38:49.810
I thought South Korea likes to talk.

38:50.140 --> 38:52.010
I'm suggesting that we should keep talking.

38:52.760 --> 38:55.460
Before the things on the paper are solved,

38:55.640 --> 38:57.020
we have no more to discuss.

38:59.450 --> 39:02.030
The things that are written here

39:02.030 --> 39:05.110
are basically that you don't want family reunions

39:06.110 --> 39:11.120
and don't want to have South-North talks anymore.

39:11.120 --> 39:13.010
Do I understand correctly?

39:16.310 --> 39:18.970
The thing I like about the North-South discussions

39:19.340 --> 39:21.440
is that we don't need a translator.

39:22.180 --> 39:27.960
I'll consider that I have my answer now and I'll be off.

39:30.540 --> 39:32.300
Why don't you sit down?

39:34.730 --> 39:38.300
You need to see this before you go.

39:42.240 --> 39:45.790
You earned some money while using your soldiers.

39:46.530 --> 39:48.870
How many zeroes?

40:05.130 --> 40:06.000
What's going on?

40:06.290 --> 40:07.860
We've been ordered to take you

40:07.860 --> 40:10.410
and Captain An back to Pyongyang immediately.

40:11.210 --> 40:14.500
Is Captain An still alive?

40:39.620 --> 40:44.990
I'll bury the secret with the traitor's body forever.

40:45.320 --> 40:50.800
Can you get it from Okryugwan in the Koryeo Hotel?

40:57.070 --> 41:00.480
I've got the password. The password is...

41:00.480 --> 41:02.280
The GPS coordinates of the Pyongyang Koryeo Hotel.

41:09.990 --> 41:13.590
Your shooting technique sucks.

41:17.020 --> 41:19.250
You shot the spot that wouldn't kill me.

41:26.260 --> 41:28.890
Why don't you come with us?

41:29.910 --> 41:30.840
We got an order.

41:30.840 --> 41:33.310
If you do anything stupid, we're going to take your body back.

41:35.050 --> 41:36.280
Can you give me two minutes?

41:37.290 --> 41:39.220
Let me have a snack before I leave.

41:43.130 --> 41:48.920
I'll pay for this snack in the other world.

41:50.590 --> 41:51.880
Thanks to you,

41:52.910 --> 41:55.030
I can go back to the Republic

41:55.990 --> 41:57.940
and die as a warrior.

42:02.650 --> 42:04.110
Thank you.

42:37.900 --> 42:39.370
Director Choi cancelled the afternoon schedule

42:39.370 --> 42:41.030
and went back to Pyongyang immediately.

42:41.030 --> 42:42.570
I'm not surprised.

42:43.250 --> 42:45.710
By the way, can we hand over an important prototype

42:45.710 --> 42:47.920
over a political matter like this?

42:47.920 --> 42:50.290
Why not? We've made lots of copies.

42:52.030 --> 42:54.970
I know this guy General Park who's on bad terms with Director Choi.

42:55.340 --> 42:57.720
I sent him a copy by e-mail.

42:58.180 --> 43:00.210
Korea is an advanced IT nation.

43:00.990 --> 43:04.060
Politics is based on ethics.

43:04.290 --> 43:06.950
A bad guy should pay for what he did.

43:07.390 --> 43:09.650
Right prevails in the end.

43:09.950 --> 43:14.090
What about the ethics of keeping your word on political trade?

43:14.460 --> 43:15.970
You have a long way to go yet.

43:15.970 --> 43:17.970
You don't do politics while following ethics.

43:20.370 --> 43:22.140
What time is the press conference?

43:23.220 --> 43:25.100
I need to change my tie.

43:26.570 --> 43:27.740
Here she comes. 10 meters!

43:30.550 --> 43:32.230
Hurry up! Five meters!

43:33.970 --> 43:35.420
I can't take my pants off because of this cast.

43:35.420 --> 43:36.830
Why did you put it back on?

43:36.830 --> 43:38.000
For the perfect crime.

43:38.000 --> 43:38.890
One meter!

43:39.940 --> 43:40.700
Lie down!

43:50.110 --> 43:51.670
He just fell asleep.

43:52.730 --> 43:54.110
Sleeping is good.

43:55.640 --> 43:58.690
He didn't go outside while I was gone,

43:59.190 --> 44:01.460
did he?

44:01.460 --> 44:02.580
I'll come back when he wakes up.

44:12.420 --> 44:13.950
That was close.

44:16.560 --> 44:17.570
Help me, Deputy!

44:17.570 --> 44:19.660
Why did you put it back on?

44:19.660 --> 44:21.020
I didn't get hurt because I wanted to.

44:26.660 --> 44:28.660
He just fell asleep.

44:29.730 --> 44:30.900
That’s right.

44:31.810 --> 44:34.610
Thank you for taking care of him, Sergeant Seo.

44:38.930 --> 44:40.150
I feel so stupid for trusting you two.

44:40.150 --> 44:41.820
I had a good sleep.

44:43.600 --> 44:45.490
What are you doing here?

44:59.370 --> 45:01.080
The perfect crime?

45:02.630 --> 45:04.080
How are you going to pay for the window?

45:04.080 --> 45:05.830
I have a good idea.

45:06.680 --> 45:08.260
Why don't you pay for half like a man?

45:08.710 --> 45:11.730
You're kidding me, right?

45:11.730 --> 45:12.850
I took a pay cut.

45:12.850 --> 45:14.780
I'm not like a man.

45:24.330 --> 45:25.180
What are you doing here?

45:26.840 --> 45:27.800
It's been a while.

45:28.400 --> 45:29.520
How have you been?

45:30.240 --> 45:32.660
My life is full of surprises.

45:32.660 --> 45:33.830
To see Shi Jin?

45:33.830 --> 45:35.970
Yes. He's not dead yet?

45:35.970 --> 45:39.200
Not yet. I might kill him soon.

45:39.900 --> 45:42.270
Go on. Sergeant Seo is visiting him now.

45:42.270 --> 45:43.590
I saw his car while I was parking. So...

45:43.630 --> 45:46.820
So?

45:46.820 --> 45:50.250
Did you have a fight with him?

45:50.250 --> 45:52.890
No. I broke up with him.

45:53.570 --> 45:55.120
He's none of my concern anymore.

45:55.370 --> 45:57.320
Really? Why? Since when?

45:58.640 --> 45:59.650
I guess.

45:59.650 --> 46:01.450
What's that supposed to mean?

46:01.450 --> 46:02.960
I understand.

46:03.410 --> 46:04.650
Room 710.

46:05.150 --> 46:07.730
Those two are dumb and dumber.

46:08.330 --> 46:11.130
I hope their country doesn't know how they really are.

46:12.130 --> 46:13.840
Is Sergeant Seo okay?

46:15.740 --> 46:17.630
You said he was none of your concern.

46:18.020 --> 46:19.760
I'm asking you as a doctor.

46:20.140 --> 46:21.960
By the way, I'm going to see Shi Jin.

46:27.560 --> 46:29.130
My heart goes out to you.

46:38.590 --> 46:39.340
Am I the only one

46:39.340 --> 46:40.560
who can't breathe  here?

46:42.770 --> 46:44.580
If you came to see me,

46:44.580 --> 46:46.830
pay attention to me.

46:46.830 --> 46:49.300
You have a girlfriend who pays attention to you.

46:49.300 --> 46:50.300
Should I go get her?

46:50.760 --> 46:51.640
No.

46:52.400 --> 46:53.920
She's been worried about me too much.

46:53.920 --> 46:55.780
I know you're okay.

46:56.520 --> 46:57.890
I'm going to leave now.

47:01.090 --> 47:02.780
You didn't have to do this.

47:02.780 --> 47:04.310
Wow, this will give me energy.

47:04.640 --> 47:06.960
Why don't you offer her a seat?

47:07.670 --> 47:08.790
Why don't you two talk?

47:08.790 --> 47:09.750
I'm leaving.

47:10.500 --> 47:11.470
I'm leaving.

47:11.470 --> 47:12.490
I'm leaving.

47:12.490 --> 47:15.170
If both of you leave, who's going to stay with me?

47:17.570 --> 47:19.830
I wish he were lying here instead of you.

47:20.530 --> 47:22.640
He was lying here instead of me for a second.

47:23.540 --> 47:24.770
You must want to know

47:24.770 --> 47:26.410
how pretty Sergeant Seo was

47:27.550 --> 47:30.340
while putting his hair back.

47:30.340 --> 47:31.450
It’s a joke.

47:32.540 --> 47:34.750
He puts his hair back with such expression and

47:35.360 --> 47:37.860
went "Oops!"

47:37.860 --> 47:39.290
I didn't say, "Oops!"

47:41.120 --> 47:42.480
You are dumb and dumber.

47:42.480 --> 47:43.670
Take care of yourself.

47:46.840 --> 47:48.020
Idiot.

47:50.050 --> 47:52.340
I tried my best to make her stay.

47:52.340 --> 47:53.700
I know. I tried to stop you.

47:55.070 --> 47:57.300
This isn't the way to go?

47:58.180 --> 47:59.420
What is it?

48:00.240 --> 48:01.570
Why did you two break up?

48:01.570 --> 48:04.470
I'm going to retire from the army.

48:07.340 --> 48:07.980
What?

48:07.980 --> 48:09.780
That's the only option

48:10.160 --> 48:11.390
that I have.

48:15.380 --> 48:16.560
You're going to do what?

48:20.630 --> 48:21.850
I'm sorry.

48:24.680 --> 48:26.950
How can you decide something like this alone?

48:29.490 --> 48:30.990
I feel hurt.

48:32.300 --> 48:33.530
I'm sorry.

48:33.800 --> 48:35.330
Does Commander Yoon know?

48:36.490 --> 48:39.180
When I was talking to him, Myung Joo was there.

48:44.740 --> 48:45.930
Go get her.

48:46.830 --> 48:48.600
She's the love of your life.

48:49.660 --> 48:51.580
Don't make her wait too long.

49:46.880 --> 49:49.220
What do you think they're doing?

49:49.830 --> 49:51.140
As far as I can tell,

49:53.640 --> 49:54.340
they had a fight

49:54.340 --> 49:58.140
and Lieutenant Yoon broke up with him. For Sergeant Seo.

49:58.750 --> 50:01.810
That's why Lieutenant Yoon can't let him win.

50:03.530 --> 50:07.000
Because Lieutenant Yoon is a good woman.

50:09.980 --> 50:11.180
As far as I can tell.

50:12.450 --> 50:15.200
Sergeant Seo knows where Lieutenant Yoon's hiding.

50:16.130 --> 50:17.670
He wants to stop her,

50:17.670 --> 50:19.290
but he isn't.

50:20.250 --> 50:23.890
So Lieutenant Yoon can save face while hiding.

50:26.140 --> 50:30.430
Because Sergeant Seo is a good man.

50:31.550 --> 50:32.480
What are you doing after work?

50:33.100 --> 50:35.130
If you're free, let's go shopping together.

50:35.130 --> 50:36.370
What are you buying?

50:37.440 --> 50:39.190
Are you buying a car?

50:39.190 --> 50:40.970
I told you I'd get a new car when I got back.

50:40.970 --> 50:42.590
I don't know when I'm going to die.

50:42.590 --> 50:43.680
I won't be too frugal.

50:43.680 --> 50:44.830
I'll spend it all before I die.

50:44.830 --> 50:47.170
I won't leave any behind and spend it all.

50:47.170 --> 50:48.850
What if you're still alive after spending it all?

50:50.320 --> 50:51.210
I haven't thought that far ahead,

50:51.210 --> 50:52.500
but I'm still buying a new car.

50:52.500 --> 50:55.910
Look around. Which is your favorite?

50:59.340 --> 51:00.490
I like this one.

51:01.590 --> 51:02.560
Huh? You interfered with my life.

51:02.560 --> 51:03.630
Why? Do you like me?

51:04.740 --> 51:06.440
That man recommended it to you earlier.

51:06.810 --> 51:07.630
Huh? You paid attention.

51:07.630 --> 51:08.620
Why? Do you like me?

51:08.620 --> 51:09.400
Yes.

51:09.400 --> 51:10.580
Huh? You said you liked me?

51:10.580 --> 51:12.010
Why? Why do you like me?

51:12.010 --> 51:13.630
Huh? What?

51:14.900 --> 51:16.510
- Oh my!
- Finish the deal.I'm hungry.

51:18.080 --> 51:21.540
Give me the contract. Now.

51:25.470 --> 51:27.330
Today, the North and South agreed on a meeting

51:27.330 --> 51:28.470
where 100 families will get together.

51:28.470 --> 51:31.050
They're now planning to hold family reunions that have been on hold for five years.

52:13.700 --> 52:15.680
Don't be scared. I got off work today.

52:15.680 --> 52:16.980
Aren't you going home?

52:17.390 --> 52:20.140
I'm your guardian until today.

52:22.260 --> 52:23.570
When can I go home?

52:23.730 --> 52:25.440
Can I stay here for another week?

52:25.830 --> 52:26.790
For other excuse.

52:26.790 --> 52:28.560
You come to see me every two hours.

52:28.560 --> 52:29.710
It's so nice to see you so often.

52:29.710 --> 52:32.130
If it's nice, why did you leave?

52:33.510 --> 52:34.830
Where did you go earlier today?

52:35.920 --> 52:36.900
I went to the rooftop.

52:36.900 --> 52:38.140
I've been to the rooftop.

52:39.050 --> 52:41.580
I didn't say of this building.

52:43.410 --> 52:46.560
Did you go to a department store?

52:51.210 --> 52:52.720
With your friend?

52:56.140 --> 52:57.730
Why did you come back by yourself?

53:00.440 --> 53:02.260
We have separate roads to take.

53:06.510 --> 53:07.550
I feel a little gloomy.

53:08.770 --> 53:10.690
Can't you try to make me feel better?

53:12.210 --> 53:13.270
Why do you feel gloomy?

53:16.000 --> 53:17.630
Peace has been restored on the Korean Peninsula

53:19.250 --> 53:22.320
but I don't know whether he's dead or alive.

53:23.700 --> 53:27.690
Your girlfriend is worried about you.

53:34.760 --> 53:36.240
Have you ever lain down in a patient's bed?

53:39.050 --> 53:40.110
Come on up.

53:42.850 --> 53:44.750
How could she reject me?

53:46.490 --> 53:48.500
Are you going to be difficult like that?

53:48.500 --> 53:50.100
I'm a patient.

53:50.490 --> 53:51.970
What do you think I'm capable of?

53:51.970 --> 53:55.260
If the patient can go to a department store,

53:55.650 --> 53:58.260
the doctor should take care of herself.

53:58.260 --> 53:59.430
What are you talking about?

53:59.430 --> 54:02.730
I don't know. I'm tired.

54:11.090 --> 54:14.700
Chi Hoon became a father today.

54:15.800 --> 54:17.070
It's a boy.

54:18.530 --> 54:20.960
If you want to buy him a gift, keep that in mind.

54:22.670 --> 54:24.030
He must be cute if he takes after his dad.

54:26.350 --> 54:27.540
Congratulate him for me.

54:29.470 --> 54:31.110
Copy that.

54:32.550 --> 54:38.830
Sorry to have worried you.

54:39.420 --> 54:43.060
Thank you for saving my life.

54:51.560 --> 54:53.090
Why do we

54:53.860 --> 54:56.380
keep saying these things?

54:57.850 --> 54:59.680
Other couples say

55:00.950 --> 55:03.050
"Thank you for taking me home."

55:03.930 --> 55:08.260
"Thank you for the anniversary present."

55:10.740 --> 55:11.940
I'm sorry.

55:11.940 --> 55:13.080
Seriously?

55:15.090 --> 55:16.580
What do you mean?

55:17.730 --> 55:20.500
I saw the peace

55:21.900 --> 55:24.290
that you protected on the news.

55:25.750 --> 55:30.640
If you really feel sorry for me,

55:33.450 --> 55:37.480
don't show up covering in blood.

55:40.740 --> 55:42.670
Please.

55:44.420 --> 55:46.010
Copy that.

55:51.450 --> 55:53.950
Do you want to see the movie we couldn't watch?

55:54.780 --> 55:55.950
Here?

55:57.490 --> 56:00.010
The VIP rooms

56:03.630 --> 56:05.160
have this cool thing.

56:08.440 --> 56:13.980
Wow, we can finally watch this movie.

56:13.980 --> 56:16.340
I never imagined it. We're actually starting the movie.

56:16.710 --> 56:18.450
Last time, you paid for it and that was it.

56:19.460 --> 56:20.620
Here we go.

56:28.210 --> 56:32.470
I don't know who fell asleep first

56:34.040 --> 56:37.020
but it was a long day

56:37.020 --> 56:39.620
and I was in his arms.

56:41.330 --> 56:44.540
I was shining in his arms all night long.

56:45.630 --> 56:47.780
Like a woman who's loved.

56:49.320 --> 56:51.420
Did the movie that we couldn't finish

56:52.480 --> 56:58.790
have a happy ending or a sad ending?

57:19.160 --> 57:22.690
-=Next Episode-=

57:22.690 --> 57:23.930
Why are you still dressed?

57:23.930 --> 57:25.060
Aren't you taking a shower?

57:25.060 --> 57:26.180
I want to see you

57:26.180 --> 57:27.290
fill the tub first.

57:27.290 --> 57:28.190
Don't even think about it.

57:28.190 --> 57:29.560
You know what?

57:29.560 --> 57:31.940
We've never said "I love you" to each other.

57:31.940 --> 57:33.760
We have, with gestures.

57:33.760 --> 57:36.090
I'm sending you on this operation.

57:36.560 --> 57:41.050
If not, I can sign the paper that you'll retire from the army now.

57:41.050 --> 57:42.120
What do you want me to do?

57:42.120 --> 57:43.590
I want to go.

57:43.590 --> 57:46.660
I'll come back when the seasons change.

57:46.660 --> 57:48.220
Sergeant Seo! You're back!

57:49.760 --> 57:52.380
Sergeant Choi, what are you doing here?
